I also experimented with a native impl. I'm not opposed to adding this, or helping to get a native ext written in C and Java versions. The JRuby version is pretty simple.

JRuby impl:

```java
    @JRubyMethod
    public IRubyObject secure_compare(ThreadContext context, IRubyObject other) {
        Ruby runtime = context.runtime;
        
        if (!(other instanceof RubyString)) return runtime.getFalse();
        
        ByteList a = value;
        ByteList b = ((RubyString)other).value;
        
        if (a.getRealSize() != b.getRealSize()) return runtime.getFalse();
        
        boolean ok = true;
        for (int i = 0; i < a.getRealSize(); i++) {
            ok = ok && (a.get(i) == b.get(i));
        }
        
        return runtime.newBoolean(ok);
    }
```

