> so the conclusion is to use `is_a?`, right?

@ka8725 not for performance reasons. The benchmarks posted above are flawed in that they assume `prefixes` is always a `String`, which is not realistic. Actually `String ===` is probably more performant since it works better with Ruby VM's inline cashes (which will probably get busted whenever `prefixes` is not a `String`, so a previously cached `String#is_a?` method needs to be discarded and a new for example `Array#is_a?` method needs to be stored in).

On the other side, I almost would never use `String === thing` instead of much more readable `thing.kind_of?(String)`.

